         <abstract id="aspace_e9e953081232a1c2bdac8115e185836c">The papers consist of three writings by Frank Altschul: memorandum on the French foreign exchange situation (1924), the typescript of his book <title render="italic">
               <part>Let No Wave Engulf Us</part>
            </title> (1941), and an invitation to Donald G. Wing to a dinner in honor of Bernhard Knollenberg.</abstract>
